{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2017-3-18-react-random-squares-avatar/2017-3-18-react-random-squares-avatar/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Its my Code Blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"bd62ec38-471a-5d86-b87c-2451999d2110","excerpt":"react-random-squares-avatar A simple react component that creates a Slack like avatar. Demo & Examples Live demo: reactrandomsquaresavatar-demo.firebaseapp.comâ€¦","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7a388bb2b771b25dabe152591ef44b84/91043/react-random-squares-avatar.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 67.3611111111111%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text \"\n        title=\"React Random Squares Avatar\"\n        src=\"/static/7a388bb2b771b25dabe152591ef44b84/799d3/react-random-squares-avatar.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7a388bb2b771b25dabe152591ef44b84/00d96/react-random-squares-avatar.png 148w,\n/static/7a388bb2b771b25dabe152591ef44b84/0b23c/react-random-squares-avatar.png 295w,\n/static/7a388bb2b771b25dabe152591ef44b84/799d3/react-random-squares-avatar.png 590w,\n/static/7a388bb2b771b25dabe152591ef44b84/91043/react-random-squares-avatar.png 720w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h1>react-random-squares-avatar</h1>\n<p>A simple react component that creates a Slack like avatar.</p>\n<h2>Demo &#x26; Examples</h2>\n<p>Live demo: <a href=\"https://reactrandomsquaresavatar-demo.firebaseapp.com/\">reactrandomsquaresavatar-demo.firebaseapp.com/</a></p>\n<h2>Github</h2>\n<p>Github repo:\n<a href=\"https://github.com/NicholasMurray/react-random-squares-avatar\">https://github.com/NicholasMurray/react-random-squares-avatar</a></p>\n<h2>NPM</h2>\n<p>NPM Package:\n<a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-random-squares-avatar/\">https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-random-squares-avatar/</a></p>\n<p>To build and test locally, run:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm install\nnpm test\nnpm run testonly\nnpm run lint\nnpm run prepublish</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>The easiest way to use react-random-squares-avatar is to install it from NPM and include it in your own React build process (using <a href=\"http://browserify.org\">Browserify</a>, <a href=\"http://webpack.github.io/\">Webpack</a>, <a href=\"http://brunch.io/\">Brunch</a>, etc).</p>\n<p>You can also use the standalone build by including <code class=\"language-text\">dist/index.js</code> in your page. If you use this, make sure you have already included React, and it is available as a global variable.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm install react-random-squares-avatar --save</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>If no props are supplied then the default height and width are 100px and the rotation will be a random 10 digit number in the range of 10 degrees to 80 degrees inclusive.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">&lt; ReactRandomSquaresAvatar /&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>The props height and width set the avatars dimensions and the rotate value can be either 0, or a 10 digit number in the range of 10 degrees to 80 degrees inclusive.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;ReactRandomSquaresAvatar height=&quot;200&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; rotate=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;ReactRandomSquaresAvatar height=&quot;200&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; rotate=&quot;80&quot; /&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Credits</h2>\n<p>Inspired by this codepen</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://codepen.io/richardj/pen/oxvrwr\">http://codepen.io/richardj/pen/oxvrwr</a> by @richardj</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"React Random Squares Avatar","date":"March 18, 2017","description":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/2017-3-18-react-random-squares-avatar/2017-3-18-react-random-squares-avatar/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2016-8-04-es6-let-there-be-let/2016-8-04-es6-let-there-be-let/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ES6 Let there be let"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2019-1-13-big-o-notation-with-javascript/2019-1-13-big-o-notation-with-javascript/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Big-O notation with Javascript"}}}}}